author: eTN Global Editor
title: Bird strike causes emergency landing at SeaTac
text:
Bird strike causes emergency landing at SeaTac     
SEATTLE, WA - Delta Air Lines jet made an emergency landing at SeaTac airport after the pilot reported that the aircraft hit at least one bird. 
The plane that was flying from Seattle to Hong Kong was forced to return to Seattle-Tacoma International Airport, where it landed safely at approximately 4:20pm.
